<TITLE> HC orders steps against chemical ripening </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court has ordered the government to take measures against those ripening fruits with toxic chemicals in reply to a public interest petition. The bench of Justice AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and Justice Md Delwar Hossain on Monday ordered the government to identify warehouses and depots involved in artificially ripening fruits and take legal action. The court also ordered the ministries of commerce, food and home to each form a committee and submit a joint report within 15 days recommending measures to prevent the use of chemicals to artificially ripen fruits. bdnews
